see Tips)","60 g rice wine vinegar","40 g white sugar","500 g water, plus extra 1 tablespoon","2 carrots, peeled and cut into julienne","2 - 4 spring onions\/shallots, trimmed and cut into thin slices","4 radishes, cut into julienne","8 tortillas (small)","fresh coriander, leaves only"]}],"id":"r150496","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-K6bqNhhkcFw\/XZQxoPQeZnI\/AAAAAAAAcw8\/8blZRv-scwIL3VpagnZRJdeWkRmOUYeFgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_wkPU_Hc38XOFQn3l.png","title":"Fish tacos with Kewpie mayonnaise","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"39.8 g","fat":"29.4 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18.2 g","calories":"2165 kJ \/ 515 kcal"},"usefulItems":"jug, sealable container, large bowl, bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["We recommend a firm white fish for this recipe such as ling or snapper.","For best results, Kewpie mayonnaise ingredients should be at room temperature. You can store leftover mayonnaise in the refrigerator for up to 3 days.","You can also use the <i>Miso coleslaw<\/i> in these tacos (please refer to the recipe on this recipe chip). Just replace the pickled vegetables with the coleslaw."],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","1h 30m","4 portions"]}